(i) whether the SANASA Development Bank is subject to regulation of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka;
(ii) whether the SANASA Development Bank has introduced a loan scheme called "Uththamachara" for retired military officers;

(vi) the minimum and the maximum repayment periods of the loans?

(i) whether he is aware that the recipients of loans have had to pay a greater amount of interest than the amount of loan as a result of extending the loan recovery period during the COVID-19 pandemic;

(iii) whether banks can give such an extension at its discretion; and
(iv) whether justice will be served to the persons who have been aggrieved by this measure?

interview . Sir, in fact, I must mention about the concept of differentiation of nations, how they are using their cultural and civilizational values to differentiate their nations. So, if we are to go rainbow, we can go to America and be rainbow. However, not even America

is rainbow. I must say that they are more culturally sensitive to their beliefs than most of you all are. The Americans believe that theirs is a civilization of white Christians. , this is the Ramazan season and it is important that we discuss an issue here. I saw the Cardinal on media once again. When you clearly observe the Easter attack, you understand that there is some fundamental misunderstanding, an error of judgement. That is why, from time to time, he comes and gives statements.

, - Buddhism - as you know, does not compete with any other religion. If you take Islam, Christianity or Judaism, they are competitive religions in the world, unfortunately, as much as you and I would love to see religions not competing with each other. The Bible, The Quran and the Torah believe in the same God, but the Messengers in them are different. In our case, Buddhism does not compete with any other religion. Therefore, we should use the full potential of that opportunity to build an inclusive nation so that we could give an example to the rest of the world. If we had done mistakes for various reasons, we have got to correct them, for sure, I agree. So many politicians are responsible for that, I agree; political parties are responsible for that, I agree. But, that does not mean that we must continue to make the same mistakes.
In that context, Sir, I must say this.
